Auci-non: Possibly by St. Ambrose (340-397). Mmmz: Iambie dimeter. TRANSLATION by Cardinal Newman. There are about twenty translations. LITURGICAL Usu: Hymn for Teroe daily throughout the year. In this hymn we ask the Holy spirit to take possession of our hearts and inflame them with the fire of divine love. It is appropriate as a hymn for Tereo, the Third Hour, for it was at that hour (9:00 A. M.) on Pentecost Day, that the Holy Ghost de· scended upon the Apostles (Acts 2, 15).
